\par {\b Where to put the files
\par }
\par Copy all the files into a single directory of your hard disk, for example, {\f5 c:}{\f5 \\}{\f5 calmira}.  Avoid putting these in your Windows directory.
\par 
\par The INI files are constantly modified, so the directory must have write permission/access.  (If you received the files on a CD-ROM, they might have the read-only bit set, so use File Manager to remove them from the copies).
\par 
\par {\b 3D controls library}{\b 
\par }
\par Calmira requires {\f5 ctl3dv2.dll}, which is supplied in a ZIP file.  If you don't already have this file in your {\f5 \\}{\f5 windows}{\f5 \\}{\f5 system} directory, unzip it to there.  Do not leave {\f5 ctl3dv2.dll }in the same directory as Calmira.

\par 
\par {\b Setting up the shell}{\b 
\par }
\par If you don't need Program Manager any more, you can use Calmira as the Windows shell.  You need to modify the {\f5 system.ini} file in your Windows directory, so make a backup copy first.  In the {\f5 [boot]}
 section there is a line which reads something like:
\par 
\par {\f5 shell=c:}{\f5 \\}{\f5 windows}{\f5 \\}{\f5 progman.exe}{\f5 
\par }
\par Comment this out by adding a semi-colon in front of it, and add a line pointing to Calmira, for example
\par 
\par {\f5 ;shell=c:}{\f5 \\}{\f5 windows}{\f5 \\}{\f5 progman.exe}{\f5 
\par }{\f5 shell=c:}{\f5 \\}{\f5 calmira}{\f5 \\}{\f5 calmira.exe}{\f5 
\par }
\par Exit to DOS and restart Windows for the new shell to take effect.  If you encounter problems when loading Windows, reset the shell to Program Manager.
