\par \pard\plain \s5 \f2\fs20\lang2057 
\par This contains the disk drives which have been detected, plus some useful programs.  When you close the system window, Calmira will close down.  
\par 
\par \{bml system.bmp\}
\par 
\par {\b Settings dialogs}{\b 
\par }
\par The system window is the centre of Calmira, and if you right click between the icons, a popup menu appears, which lets you access dialogs to configure the program.  These dialog boxes are often accessible from elsewhere but you can always open them from h
ere.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn \b\f2\cf2\lang2057 \page {\plain \f3\fs16\up6\lang2057 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang2057 {\fs16\up6 #} IconWindows}} {\plain \f3\fs16\up6\lang2057 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang2057 {\fs16\up6 $}
 Icon windows}} {\plain \f3\fs16\up6\lang2057 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang2057 {\fs16\up6 K} icon windows; icons; windows}} Icon windows
\par \pard\plain \s5 \f2\fs20\lang2057 
\par These provide the facilities for managing your files.  Each window displays the contents of one folder, and each folder may only be shown by one window.  If you try and open a folder which is already displayed, the existing window is restored and brought 
to the front, as required.
\par 
\par \{bml iconwin.bmp\}
\par 
\par If you right click over an icon, the {\i object menu} appears.  Commands in the top half affect all selected objects, those in the bottom half work on the focused object.  If you right click in the space between icons or the grey window border, the {\i 
window menu} appears.  These commands affect the icon window or the folder it represents.
\par 
\par To open the parent folder, press Backspace.  To close or arrange groups of windows, see the {\uldb keyboard commands}{\v KeyCommands} summary .
\par 
\par {\b Managing files and folders}{\b 
\par }
\par First {\uldb select}{\v SelectingObjects} the objects which you want to w
ork with.  To delete, rename or describe them, pick the appropriate command from the object menu.  To copy, drag the icons to the destination (either a window or another icon).  If you right-click during the drag, the operation is toggled between a copy a
nd a move.
\par 
